
This comes from:

http://code.google.com/p/shared-space/wiki/JiraExtendedWebservice

Build with maven2 after Atlassian repository has been configured.

http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DEVNET/How+to+Build+an+Atlassian+Plugin

In short:

- Get the SDK from http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DEVNET/Setting+up+your+Plugin+Development+Environment
- Unpack the tar.gz file and cd into the resulting directory.
- Add the ./bin to your PATH
- Run "atlas-cli", this will set up the environment
- cd back to this project
- mvn install
- scp the target/webservice*jar to jira instance WEB-INF/lib/
- restart jira

